olive oil
2 radish
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 packet tahini
1 packet Garlic Dip
2 flatbreads
1 packet pulled chicken
1 sachet Middle Eastern spice blend
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 bag parsley
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
½ sachet Turkish Sumac Seasoning

• Thinly slice radish and cucumber.
Roughly chop tomato
• In a small bowl, combine tahini and
garlic dip
• Toast or grill flatbreads to your liking

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat. Cook chicken and Middle
Eastern seasoning until browned
and fragrant, 3-4 mins
• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad
leaves, radish, cucumber, tomato,
chicken mixture and balsamic
dressing

• Slice flatbreads into quarters
• Divide chicken salad between bowls.
Top with almonds and torn parsley
• Drizzle over tahini-garlic sauce.
Sprinkle over sumac seasoning
(1/2 sachet for 2P / 1 sachet for 4P)
• Serve with flatbreads